webwork-tex.statement:
			{\bf 13. {\footnotesize (1 point) \path|Library/Rochester/setDiscrete4Functions/ur_dis_4_3.pg|}}\newline \par 
Determine if each of the following functions from \(\lbrace a,b,c,d
\rbrace\) to itself is one-to-one and/or onto. \leavevmode\\\relax 
Check ALL correct answers. \leavevmode\\\relax 
(a) \(f(a)=c, f(b)=d, f(c)=a\)
\par 

\begin{itemize}
\item{A. onto.}
\item{B. one-to-one.}
\item{C. neither one-to-one nor onto.}

\end{itemize}

\par 
\(f(a)=d, f(b)=a, f(c)=c, f(d)=b\)
\par 

\begin{itemize}
\item{A. neither one-to-one nor onto.}
\item{B. onto.}
\item{C. one-to-one.}

\end{itemize}

\par 
\(f(a)=b, f(b)=b, f(c)=d, f(d)=c\)
\par 

\begin{itemize}
\item{A. onto.}
\item{B. neither one-to-one nor onto.}
\item{C. one-to-one.}

\end{itemize}
